üì± 1. Fitness Tracker App (Workout + Nutrition Tracker)
üîπ Overview

A simple Android app to:

Log workouts (exercise name, duration, calories burned)

Track meals and total calorie intake

Show daily summary

üîπ Main Features

Two activities: WorkoutActivity and MealActivity

SQLite Database for storage

Dashboard for total calories

üß© Project Structure
FitnessTracker/
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ MainActivity.java
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ WorkoutActivity.java
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ MealActivity.java
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ DatabaseHelper.java
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ activity_main.xml
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ activity_workout.xml
 ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ activity_meal.xml

üß† MainActivity.java
package com.example.fitnesstracker;

import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.TextView;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {
    TextView totalCalories;
    DatabaseHelper db;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
        totalCalories = findViewById(R.id.txtTotalCalories);
        db = new DatabaseHelper(this);
        updateCalories();
    }

    public void openWorkout(View v){
        startActivity(new Intent(this, WorkoutActivity.class));
    }

    public void openMeal(View v){
        startActivity(new Intent(this, MealActivity.class));
    }

    private void updateCalories(){
        int total = db.getTotalCalories();
        totalCalories.setText("Today's Calories: " + total);
    }
}

‚öôÔ∏è DatabaseHelper.java
package com.example.fitnesstracker;

import android.content.Context;
import android.database.sqlite.SQLiteDatabase;
import android.database.sqlite.SQLiteOpenHelper;
import android.database.Cursor;
import android.content.ContentValues;

public class DatabaseHelper extends SQLiteOpenHelper {
    public static final String DB_NAME = "fitness.db";
    public static final String TABLE_NAME = "calories";

    public DatabaseHelper(Context context) {
        super(context, DB_NAME, null, 1);
    }

    @Override
    public void onCreate(SQLiteDatabase db) {
        db.execSQL("CREATE TABLE " + TABLE_NAME + "(id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, type TEXT, calories INTEGER)");
    }

    @Override
    public void onUpgrade(SQLiteDatabase db, int oldVersion, int newVersion) {
        db.execSQL("DROP TABLE IF EXISTS " + TABLE_NAME);
        onCreate(db);
    }

    public void insertData(String type, int calories) {
        SQLiteDatabase db = this.getWritableDatabase();
        ContentValues cv = new ContentValues();
        cv.put("type", type);
        cv.put("calories", calories);
        db.insert(TABLE_NAME, null, cv);
    }

    public int getTotalCalories() {
        SQLiteDatabase db = this.getReadableDatabase();
        Cursor cursor = db.rawQuery("SELECT SUM(calories) FROM " + TABLE_NAME, null);
        cursor.moveToFirst();
        return cursor.getInt(0);
    }
}

üó£Ô∏è 2. Language Learning App (Quiz-Based)
üîπ Overview

A simple quiz-style app for learning words:

Display a question (word meaning)

User chooses the correct answer

Score is updated

üß† MainActivity.java
package com.example.languageapp;

import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.*;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {
    TextView question, score;
    Button opt1, opt2, opt3;
    int current = 0, points = 0;

    String[] words = {"Bonjour", "Gracias", "Hallo"};
    String[][] options = {{"Hello", "Goodbye", "Thank you"},
                          {"Please", "Thank you", "Sorry"},
                          {"Bye", "Hello", "Good night"}};
    int[] answers = {0, 1, 1}; // correct option index

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
        question = findViewById(R.id.question);
        score = findViewById(R.id.score);
        opt1 = findViewById(R.id.opt1);
        opt2 = findViewById(R.id.opt2);
        opt3 = findViewById(R.id.opt3);
        loadQuestion();
    }

    private void loadQuestion() {
        if(current < words.length) {
            question.setText("Meaning of " + words[current]);
            opt1.setText(options[current][0]);
            opt2.setText(options[current][1]);
            opt3.setText(options[current][2]);
        } else {
            question.setText("Quiz Over! Final Score: " + points);
            opt1.setVisibility(View.GONE);
            opt2.setVisibility(View.GONE);
            opt3.setVisibility(View.GONE);
        }
    }

    public void checkAnswer(View v){
        Button b = (Button)v;
        int index = Integer.parseInt(b.getTag().toString());
        if(index == answers[current]){
            points++;
            score.setText("Score: " + points);
        }
        current++;
        loadQuestion();
    }
}

üí∞ 3. Personal Finance Tracker App
üîπ Overview

Track your expenses and budget using SQLite.

‚öôÔ∏è DatabaseHelper.java
package com.example.financeapp;

import android.content.Context;
import android.database.sqlite.*;
import android.content.ContentValues;
import android.database.Cursor;

public class DatabaseHelper extends SQLiteOpenHelper {
    public DatabaseHelper(Context context) {
        super(context, "finance.db", null, 1);
    }

    @Override
    public void onCreate(SQLiteDatabase db) {
        db.execSQL("CREATE TABLE expenses(id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, category TEXT, amount REAL)");
    }

    @Override
    public void onUpgrade(SQLiteDatabase db, int oldVersion, int newVersion) {
        db.execSQL("DROP TABLE IF EXISTS expenses");
        onCreate(db);
    }

    public void addExpense(String category, double amount) {
        SQLiteDatabase db = this.getWritableDatabase();
        ContentValues cv = new ContentValues();
        cv.put("category", category);
        cv.put("amount", amount);
        db.insert("expenses", null, cv);
    }

    public double getTotal() {
        SQLiteDatabase db = this.getReadableDatabase();
        Cursor c = db.rawQuery("SELECT SUM(amount) FROM expenses", null);
        c.moveToFirst();
        return c.getDouble(0);
    }
}

üß≠ How to Run These Projects

Open Android Studio ‚Üí New Project ‚Üí Empty Activity.

Replace the MainActivity.java and layout files (activity_main.xml) with the provided code.

Create new Java classes (e.g., DatabaseHelper.java).

Add necessary permissions in AndroidManifest.xml (if using storage or internet).

Run on emulator or real Android device.
